{"title_page": "Renaud (disambiguation)", "text_new": "{{Distinguish|Renault (disambiguation)}}\n{{Wiktionary pipe|Renaud}}\n'''[[Renaud]]''', born Renaud S\u00e9chan, is a French singer, songwriter and actor.\n\n'''Renaud''' may also refer to:\n* [[Renaud (given name)]], a male French given name, related to the English name [[Reynold]] or [[Ronald]]\n* [[Renaud Island]], an island in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica\n* [[Renaud (opera)]], a 1783 opera by Antonio Sacchini\n* [[Renaud, Quebec]], part of [[Laval, Quebec]]\n\n==Persons with the surname Renaud==\n* [[Francis Renaud (sculptor)]] (1887-1973), French sculptor\n* [[Francis Renaud (actor)]] (born 1967), French actor\n* [[Fran\u00e7ois Renaud]] (1923-1975), French judge, assassinated\n* [[Jean Renaud de Segrais]] (1624-1701), French poet\n* [[Line Renaud]] (born 1928), a French female singer and actress, true name Jacqueline Ent\u00e9\n* [[Michelle Renaud]] (born 1988), Mexican actress\n\n==Persons with the given name Renaud==\n* [[Renaud Laplanche]] (born 1970), French American entrepreneur and business executive\n\n== Toponyms ==\n* [[Renaud River]], a tributary of the [[Rivi\u00e8re du Gouffre]], in [[Baie-Saint-Paul]], MRC [[Charlevoix (regional county municipality)|Charlevoix]], [[Capitale-Nationale]], [[Quebec]], [[Canada]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[Reynard (disambiguation)]]\n* [[Renault (disambiguation)]]\n\n{{disambig|surname}}\n\n{{Ronald-name}}\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|Renault (disambiguation)}}\n{{Wiktionary pipe|Renaud}}\n'''[[Renaud]]''', born Renaud S\u00e9chan, is a French singer, songwriter and actor.\n\n'''Renaud''' may also refer to:\n* [[Renaud (given name)]], a male French given name, related to the English name [[Reynold]] or [[Ronald]]\n* [[Renaud Island]], an island in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica\n* [[Renaud (opera)]], a 1783 opera by Antonio Sacchini\n* [[Renaud, Quebec]], part of [[Laval, Quebec]]\n\n==Persons with the surname Renaud==\n* [[Francis Renaud (sculptor)]] (1887-19