{"title_page": "Lesley Vance (artist)", "text_new": "'''Lesley Vance''' (born 1977, [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]])<ref name=\"blouin2017\">{{Cite news|author=|url=https://www.blouinartinfo.com/news/story/2618590/forwards-only-lesley-vance-at-xavier-hufkens-brussels|title=Forwards Only: Lesley Vance at Xavier Hufkens, Brussels|date=October 27, 2017|work=[[Blouin Artinfo]]|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref> is an American artist based in [[Los Angeles]]. \n\n==Background==\nShe attended the [[University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison]] and [[California Institute of the Arts]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.heraldst.com/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance|website=Herald St|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref>\n\nVance initially painted still lifes, but is more recently known for her intimately sized improvisational oil paintings. ''Art in America'' described her work as \"a distinctive sort of illusionistic abstraction, its visual presence a balance between elusive secret and seductive fact\".<ref name=aim2014>{{Cite news|author=Leah Ollman |url=https://www.artinamericamagazine.com/reviews/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance|work=[[Art in America]]|date=February 4, 2014 |access-date=2018-08-10}}</ref> Her work is \"rooted in the liquidity of paint and the balletic, improvisational movements of the hand\".<ref name=aim2014 />\n\n==Exhibitions==\nSolo presentations include: [[Bowdoin College Museum of Art]], Brunswick (2012);<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bowdoin.edu/art-museum/exhibitions/2012/lesley-vance.shtml|title=Lesley Vance|website=www.bowdoin.edu|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref> The FLAG Art Foundation, New York (2012);<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://flagartfoundation.org/exhibitions/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance \u2013 The FLAG Art Foundation|last=Foundation|first=Flag Art|work=The FLAG Art Foundation|access-date=2018-04-21|language=en-US}}</ref> the [[Huntington Library]], Art Collections (with [[Ricky Swallow]]); Botanical Gardens, San Marino (2012),<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.huntington.org/WebAssets/Templates/exhibitiondetail.aspx?id=20112|title=Lesley Vance & Ricky Swallow|website=www.huntington.org|access-date=2018-04-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180614045847/http://www.huntington.org/WebAssets/Templates/exhibitiondetail.aspx?id=20112|archive-date=2018-06-14|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Xavier Hufkens]] Gallery, [[Brussels]], Belgium (2012, 2014 and 2017).<ref name=\"blouin2017\" />and the David Kordanksy Gallery, Los Angeles (2013).<ref>{{Cite news|author=Sharon Mizota |url=http://articles.latimes.com/2013/nov/14/entertainment/la-et-cm-review-lesley-vance-at-david-kordansky-gallery-20131111 |title=Review: Lesley Vance's small-scale abstractions constantly surprise|work=The Los Angeles Times|date=November 14, 2013|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref> \n\nVance\u2019s work was also included in the 2010 [[Whitney Biennial]], New York<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.whitney.org/Exhibitions/2010Biennial|title=Whitney Biennial 2010 {{!}} Whitney Museum of American Art|website=www.whitney.org|language=en|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref> Her work can be found in the collection of the [[Museum of Modern Art]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.moma.org/artists/28840|title=Lesley Vance {{!}} MoMA|website=www.moma.org|language=en|access-date=2018-06-14}}</ref> [[Whitney Museum of American Art]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://collection.whitney.org/artist/11263/LesleyVance|title=Whitney Museum of American Art: Lesley Vance|website=collection.whitney.org|language=en|access-date=2018-06-14}}</ref> [[Metropolitan Museum of Art]], Los Angeles County Museum of Art and [[Hammer Museum]], among others.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.heraldst.com/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance|website=Herald St|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Vance, Lesley}}\n{{draft categories|[[Category:1977 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Artists from Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Artists from Milwaukee]]\n[[Category:University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison alumni]]\n[[Category:California Institute of the Arts alumni]]}}\n", "text_old": "'''Lesley Vance''' (born 1977, [[Milwaukee]], [[Wisconsin]])<ref name=\"blouin2017\">{{Cite news|author=|url=https://www.blouinartinfo.com/news/story/2618590/forwards-only-lesley-vance-at-xavier-hufkens-brussels|title=Forwards Only: Lesley Vance at Xavier Hufkens, Brussels|date=October 27, 2017|work=[[Blouin Artinfo]]|access-date=2019-03-10}}</ref> is an American artist based in [[Los Angeles]]. \n\n==Background==\nShe attended the [[University of Wisconsin\u2013Madison]] and [[California Institute of the Arts]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.heraldst.com/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance|website=Herald St|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref>\n\nVance initially painted still lifes, but is more recently known for her intimately sized improvisational oil paintings. ''Art in America'' described her work as \"a distinctive sort of illusionistic abstraction, its visual presence a balance between elusive secret and seductive fact\".<ref name=aim2014>{{Cite news|author=Leah Ollman |url=https://www.artinamericamagazine.com/reviews/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance|work=[[Art in America]]|date=February 4, 2014 |access-date=2018-08-10}}</ref> Her work is \"rooted in the liquidity of paint and the balletic, improvisational movements of the hand\".<ref name=aim2014 />\n\n==Exhibitions==\nSolo presentations include: [[Bowdoin College Museum of Art]], Brunswick (2012);<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.bowdoin.edu/art-museum/exhibitions/2012/lesley-vance.shtml|title=Lesley Vance|website=www.bowdoin.edu|access-date=2018-04-21}}</ref> The FLAG Art Foundation, New York (2012);<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://flagartfoundation.org/exhibitions/lesley-vance/|title=Lesley Vance \u2013 The FLAG Art Foundation|last=Foundation|first=Flag Art|work=The FLAG Art Foundation|access-date=2018-04-21|language=en-US}}</ref> the [[Huntington Library]], Art Collecti